# Cursor Rules Template (copy to project root when using Cursor)

## Usage
- Copy this file to the project root as `.cursorrules` when using Cursor IDE.
- This file guides Cursor AI on the factory structure and rules.

## Rules
1) Read `INDEX.md` first to understand structure.
2) Follow `0-agents/_core/global-rules.md`.
3) Select the correct mode (`0-agents/mode/[mode].md`).
4) Use the right agent workflow (`0-agents/agents/*.md`).
5) Keep code under `3-technical/3.4-source-code/` only.
6) Do not create files outside the defined structure.
7) Update `INDEX.md` and `8-governance/changelog.md` after structural changes.
8) Use orchestration handoff format when finishing.

## Success Criteria
- ✅ Followed agent workflow and mode rules
- ✅ Files in correct locations
- ✅ Documentation updated
- ✅ INDEX.md and changelog updated
- ✅ Handoff provided
